<p>I don't know if my question is related to overriding or polymorphism hence looking forward for someone advise.</p>  <p>Refer to the following coding, </p>  <pre><code>    Father f=new Father();     f.eat();             // display father's eat()     Son s=new Son();     s.eat();             // display Son's eat()     Father x=new Son();     x.eat();             // display Son's eat() </code></pre>  <p>It is learned that </p>  <pre><code>Son s=new Son();         s.eat(); </code></pre>  <p>and </p>  <pre><code>Father x=new Son();         x.eat(); </code></pre>  <p>would display the same result, then I wonder why some tutorial are mentioned about using </p>  <pre><code>Father x=new Son();             x.eat(); </code></pre>  <p>instead of using </p>  <pre><code>Son s=new Son();             s.eat(); </code></pre>  <p>directly? </p>